Police in BuruBuru are holding an AP officer suspected to have defiled a 15 year old secondary school girl.The officer based at Kiambiu slums AP camp was arrested on Wednesday evening after the parents of the minor complained to police.He was interrogated by DCI officers but denied the allegations.He has been locked up pending forensic investigations.Buruburu DCI boss Jeremiah Ikiao said police had taken various samples to the government chemist for analysis."We will take the officer to court today (Thursday) and seek for more time to detain him to complete investigations.It is alleged that the officer committed the offense at the AP camp on November 14th. Read: Cop in court for defilement